    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine equipped with individual throttle bodies. This driver-focused example has received critical preventative maintenance, including a comprehensive VANOS system overhaul and rear subframe reinforcement. Power is delivered through a crisp 6-speed manual transmission to a factory limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal corner-exit traction. The chassis remains composed with refreshed suspension bushings and an intact M-variable steering rack. While showing minor aesthetic patina consistent with a well-loved performance vehicle, the mechanical vitals are robust, providing the linear power delivery and telepathic handling these chassis are known for.",
